ible Hulk'' for some video releases\n|-\n| ''[[Spider-Man Strikes Back]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''The Amazing Spider-Man''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Charles Fries Productions\n| Composite of the two-part episode ''Deadly Dust''; limited theatrical release in some European and South American markets; VHS release in 1980.\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''[[Spider-Man: The Dragon's Challenge]]''\n| Composite of the two-part episode ''The Chinese Web''; limited theatrical release in Australia, Brazil, and some European markets;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=V6_uCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT13&lpg=PT13&dq=Spider-man%201978%20japanese%20theatrical&source=bl&ots=zFi5PT_KGe&sig=XYrR7WEkJst7QH9gbjx7k0JQSnw&hl=sv&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiv1czw7pnRAhWH1SwKHeqdCpoQ6AEIOzAE#v=onepage&q=Spider-man%201978%20japanese%20theatrical&f=false|title=Marvel Comics into Film: Essays on Adaptations Since the 1940s|first1=Matthew J.|last1=McEniry|first2=Robert Moses|last2=Peaslee|first3=Robert G.|last3=Weiner|date=March 30, 2016|publisher=McFarland|via=Google Books}}</ref> VHS release in 1982.\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Blade: The Series|Blade: House of Chthon]]''\n| ''[[Blade: The Series]]''\n| [[New Line Television]]\n| Released on DVD in unrated expanded format with harsher language and frontal nudity\n|- style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[Inhumans premiere|''Inhumans'']]<!--Please do not change to the ABC titles. The IMAX release did not have an official name for the release of the episodes, only calling them onscreen as Part 1 and Part 2. Hence, it should be noted as such in this context here.-->\n| ''[[Inhumans (TV series)|Inhumans]]''\n| [[ABC Studios]] /<br />[[Marvel Television]]\n| The two first episodes of the series, ''Behold... The Inhumans'' and ''Those Who Would Destroy Us'', debuted in [[IMAX]] theaters,<ref>{{cite tweet|author=[[IMAX Corporation]]|user=IMAX|number=837762369107419136|title=The full cast is set for @Marvel's #Inhumans, premiering exclusively in IMAX theatres September 1!|date=March 3